text: Anyone remember how to get Enterprise Miner to run the exhaustive decision tree that we can edit easily?
<@U1L1D4WG7> After you run the decision tree node, click on  interactive ellipsis (in the side panel)
I was looking for options before running the thing.  Do you know how to increase the purity of a node?

I've just been fiddling around with the trees manually. Like pruning stuff with very low observation counts (probably overfitting?), where the branches don't significantly change the purity, or building a tree using only 3 or 4 of the most important variables
I'm having trouble inserting variables where we want them. e.g. if we don't want a tree to start with variable A, how can we force it to use something else?
If you right click on the node,  and then click Split node, you should get all the variable options
